						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I was thinking about a possible feature: seamless bankswitches to allow more than 256 tiles per map.</div>
<br />In my game I do this manually: I have object types used to modify palettes and tiles, and when these objects are reached they just do their thing.
<br />
<br />My map editor doesn't know about this feature though, so editing such maps can be a bit tricky. I basically have to give my map editor a different tileset depending on the section of the level I'm editing, which means it's not possible to see the entire level with the correct tiles/palettes if such changes are used.</div>

